# Build & cross-compile

## Native

```bash
make deps     # clang/llvm/libelf-dev/zlib1g-dev + git submodules
make          # -> build/usbtrace (+ ./usbtrace symlink)
```

## Cross (req #5: x86 / x86_64 / arm / arm64)

```bash
make ARCH=arm64 CROSS_COMPILE=aarch64-linux-gnu- VMLINUX_BTF=/path/target/vmlinux
make ARCH=arm   CROSS_COMPILE=arm-linux-gnueabihf- VMLINUX_BTF=/path/target/vmlinux
```

## Invariants (do not break)

- `ARCH` is normalized to `x86`/`arm`/`arm64`; auto-detected from `uname -m`.
- **bpftool builds as a HOST tool** (`ARCH= CROSS_COMPILE=`): build-time only,
  never cross it.
- BPF object is CO-RE/arch-neutral; `-D__TARGET_ARCH_$(ARCH)` only selects
  `PT_REGS_*`.
- User binary uses `$(CROSS_COMPILE)gcc`; needs target `libelf`/`zlib`.
- `vmlinux.h` resolution: `VMLINUX_BTF` > `bpf/vmlinux/<arch>/vmlinux.h` >
  `/sys/kernel/btf/vmlinux`. For reproducible CI, commit per-arch headers.
- Module discovery is automatic via `find src -name '*.bpf.c'/'*.c'`; keep new
  modules inside `src/modules/<name>/` so they're picked up.

## Debugging a load failure

Run with `-v` for libbpf debug + verifier log; ensure root and BTF present.
